Han character

[edit]
See images of
Radical 72 日

日 (Kangxi radical 72, 日+0, 4 strokes, cangjie input 日 (A), four-corner 60100, composition ⿴囗一)

  1. Kangxi radical #72, ⽇.
  2. Shuowen Jiezi radical №231

Usage notes

[edit]
  • Not to be confused with 曰 (Kangxi radical #73), which is generally wider and shorter.

Chinese

Glyph origin

[edit]
Historical forms of the character 日
Shang Western Zhou Warring States Shuowen Jiezi (compiled in Han) Liushutong (compiled in Ming)
Oracle bone script Bronze inscriptions Chu slip and silk script Small seal script Transcribed ancient scripts
Characters in the same phonetic series (日) (Zhengzhang, 2003) 
Old Chinese
涅 *niːɡ
捏 *niːɡ
篞 *niːɡ
衵 *niɡ, *njiɡ
日 *njiɡ
馹 *njiɡ

Pictogram (象形) – the sun. A dot or line was added in the centre to distinguish it from visually similar characters, e.g. 囗 (early form of 丁). Compare earlier forms of the character with the astronomical and astrological symbol for the Sun (☉) and the Egyptian hieroglyph 𓇳.

From Proto-Sino-Tibetan *ku-ni(k). Cognate to Tibetan ཉི་མ (nyi ma, “sun, day”), Burmese နေ (ne, “sun”) or Burmese နေ့ (ne., “day”), S'gaw Karen နံၤ (nĩ, “day”), and Nuosu ꑍ (nyip, “day, daytime”).

Definitions

[edit]

日

  1. (astronomy) Sun
  2. daytime; time between sunrise and sunset
    日班  ―  rìbān  ―  day shift
    Antonyms: 夜 (yè), 夜間 / 夜间 (yèjiān), 夜晚 (yèwǎn), 晚上 (wǎnshang)
  3. day; twenty-four hours
  4. everyday; daily; day-to-day
  5. day of the month
    三月四日  ―  sān yuè sì rì  ―  March 4
    Synonym: 號 / 号 (hào)
  6. some day; some other time
  7. former times; previous times; the past
  8. time; period; age
  9. Classifier for days.
  10. short for 日本 (Rìběn, “Japan; Japanese; Nippo-”)
    中日詞典／中日词典  ―  zhōngrì cídiǎn  ―  Chinese-Japanese dictionary
    日式咖喱  ―  Rìshì gālí  ―  Japanese curry
  11. (obsolete on its own in Standard Chinese) alternative form of 二 (èr, “two”)
  12. (obsolete) short for 日斯巴尼亞／日斯巴尼亚 (Rìsībāníyà, “Spain”)
  13. (～母) (Chinese linguistics) the Middle Chinese initial of 日 (MC nyit)

Definitions

[edit]

日

  1. (dialectal Mandarin, dialectal Jin, dialectal Wu, dialectal Xiang, vulgar, often in abuses) to fuck; to have sexual intercourse with
    狗日  ―  gǒurì  ―  fucking
    • 我日他們十八輩兒的祖宗！ [MSC, trad.]
      我日他们十八辈儿的祖宗！ [MSC, simp.]
      From: 1944, 老舍 (Lao She), 《惶惑》 (Bewilderment), in 《四世同堂》 (Four Generations Under One Roof)
      Wǒ rì tāmen shíbā bèir de zǔzōng! [Pinyin]
      Screw their ancestors to the eighteenth generation!
    • 一句話，于瘸子把小姨日了。 [MSC, trad.]
      一句话，于瘸子把小姨日了。 [MSC, simp.]
      From: 2003, 董立勃, 风吹草低, in 《当代》, issue 4
      Yī jù huà, Yú quézi bǎ xiǎoyí rì le. [Pinyin]
      In one sentence ― Yu the Lame fucked mum's youngest sister.
    • 甚至在別人的慫恿下，對着蘇婕說，我想日你。 [MSC, trad.]
      甚至在别人的怂恿下，对着苏婕说，我想日你。 [MSC, simp.]
      From: 2004, 锦璐, 双人床, in 《当代》, issue 2
      Shènzhì zài biérén de sǒngyǒng xià, duì zhe Sū Jié shuō, wǒ xiǎng rì nǐ [Pinyin]
      At others' instigation, (he would) even say to Su Jie's face that “I want to fuck you”.
    • 2005, CCTV-1, Drawing Sword, episode 13, spoken by Li Yunlong (Li Youbin):
      山本，我日你先人！給句痛快話，投降不投降？ [MSC, trad.]
      山本，我日你先人！给句痛快话，投降不投降？ [MSC, simp.]
      Shānběn, wǒ rì nǐ xiānrén! Gěi jù tòngkuài huà, tóujiàng bù tóujiàng? [Pinyin]
      Yamamoto — fuck your ancestors! Give me a quick response: surrender or not?

Noun

[edit]

日(にち) • (nichi) 

  1. short for 日曜日 (nichiyōbi): Sunday

Counter

[edit]

日(にち) • (-nichi) 

  1. ordinal day of a month
    ２７(にじゅうしち)日(にち) ― nijūshichi-nichi ― the 27th
  2. number of days
    誕(たん)生(じょう)日(び)まであと１２(じゅうに)日(にち)だ ― tanjōbi made ato jūni-nichi da ― My birthday is in 12 days.
Usage notes
[edit]

Sometimes shortened to んち (-nchi) or ち (-chi).

Affix

[edit]

日(にち) • (nichi) 

  1. sun
  2. daytime, daylight
  3. day
  4. short for 日本 (Nihon, Nippon): Japan, Japanese, Nippo-
  5. short for 日向国 (Hyūga-no-kuni): Hyūga Province

Etymology 3

[edit]
Kanji in this term
日
ひ
Grade: 1
kun'yomi

⟨pi1⟩ → */pʲi/ → /ɸi/ → /hi/

From Old Japanese, from Proto-Japonic *pi (“day”).

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • (Tokyo) ひ [hì] (Heiban – [0])[1]
  • (Tokyo) ひ [híꜜ] (Atamadaka – [1]) when meaning “a day”, and when preceded by a modifier.
  • IPA(key): [çi]
  • Audio:(file)

Noun

[edit]

日(ひ) • (hi) 

  1. 陽: the sun
    Synonyms: 太陽 (taiyō), 日輪 (nichirin), 金烏 (kin'u)
  2. 陽: sunlight, sunshine
    Synonym: 日光 (nikkō)
  3. 陽: daytime, daylight
    Synonym: 昼間 (hiruma)
  4. a day
  5. time and date
  6. a daily (something done every day)
    Synonyms: 日々 (hibi), 毎日 (mainichi)
  7. the weather
    Synonym: 天気 (tenki)
  8. a (usually unfortunate) case, event, situation
  9. the times (age, era, or time in the past)
    Synonyms: 頃 (koro), 時代 (jidai)
  10. an auspicious or inauspicious aspect of a given day
    Synonym: 日柄 (higara)
  11. a 家紋 (kamon, “family crest”) with a sun-shaped design

Etymology 4

[edit]
Kanji in this term
日
か
Grade: 1
kun'yomi

    From Old Japanese. The forms of words created using this suffix may be evidence for an earlier *uka form, see 二日(ふつか) (futsuka), 四日(ようか) (youka, modern form 四日(よっか) (yokka)), 六日(むゆか) (muyuka, modern form 六日(むいか) (muika)), 七日(なぬか) (nanuka, modern form 七日(なのか) (nanoka)), 八日(やうか) (yauka, modern form 八日(ようか) (yōka)), 九日(ここぬか) (kokonuka, modern form 九日(ここのか) (kokonoka)), and 二十日(はつか) (hatsuka) (two, four, six, seven, eight, nine, and twenty days, respectively).[2]

    Etymology 1

    [edit]

    From Proto-Japonic *pi.

    Distinct from 火 (pi2, “fire”). See Jōdai Tokushu Kanazukai for details on Old Japanese readings.

    Noun

    [edit]

    日 (pi1) (kana ひ)

    1. the sun
    2. sunlight, sunshine
    3. daytime, daylight
    4. a day
    5. a reference to the imperial family or lineage, thought to be descended from the sun goddess Amaterasu

    Etymology 2

    [edit]

    Due to the irregularities in the derived terms, it has been speculated that the suffix was actually -uka, which makes the connection to 日 (ke) less likely.[1]

    Suffix

    [edit]

    日 (-ka) (kana か)

    1. daytimes
    2. number of days
    Derived terms
    [edit]
    • 二日 (putuka)
    • 七日 (nanuka)
    • 八日 (yaka)
    • 十日 (to2woka)
    Descendants
    [edit]
    • Japanese: 日 (-ka)

    Etymology 3

    [edit]

    Apophonic form of ka above, possibly by the fusion of ancient nominal particle い (i).

    Noun

    [edit]

    日 (ke2) (kana け)

    1. (plural only) days
      • c. 759, Man’yōshū, book 4, poem 484:
        一日社人母待吉長氣乎如此耳待者有不得勝
        pi1to1pi1 ko2so2 pi1to2 mo mati yo2ki1 nagaki1 ke2 wo kaku nomi2 mateba arikatu
        One day, people still waiting are good; if the long days' wait just this way, then they should not exist.
    Derived terms
    [edit]
    • 日長し (ke2nagasi)
    • 日竝ぶ (ke2narabu)
    • 日のころごろ (ke2 no2 ko2ro2go2ro2)
    • 朝に日に (asa ni ke2 ni)
    • 旅の日 (tabi1 no2 ke2)
